hh3cFlash.name: hh3cFlash
hh3cFlash.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cFlash.description: This MIB contains objects to manage flash cards and flash card operations. There are no constraints on this MIB.

Hh3cFlashOperationStatus.name: Hh3cFlashOperationStatus
Hh3cFlashOperationStatus.description: The status of the specified operation can be one of the following. opInProgress : The operation is in process. opSuccess : The operation has been completed successfully. opInvalid : The command is invalid or command-protocol-device combination is unsupported by the system. opInvalidProtocol : Invalid protocol is specified. opInvalidSourceName : Invalid source file name is specified. opInvalidDestName : Invalid target name is specified. opInvalidServerAddress : Invalid server address is specified. opDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeviceOpenError : Invalid device name is specified. opDeviceError : Device read, write or erase error. opDeviceNotProgrammable : Device is read-only but a write or erase operation was specified. opDeviceFull : Device is filled to capacity. opFileOpenError : Invalid file name; file not found in partition. opFileTransferError : File transfer was unsuccessful. opFileChecksumError : File checksum in Flash is invalid. opNoMemory : System is running in low on memory. opUnknownFailure : Failure which is unknown. opDeleteFileOpenError : File is in used by another process. opDeleteInvalidDevice : Invalid device name is specified. opDeleteInvalidFunction : Deleted operation is unsupported by the device. opDeleteOperationError : Operation is in a low error. opDeleteInvalidFileName : Invalid file name is specified. pDeleteDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeleteParaError : The parameters are invalid. opDeleteInvalidPath : The file path is invalid. opDeleteFileNotExistInSlave : Failed to delete file, because the file is not exist in the slave. opDeleteFileFailedInSlave : Operation is fail when delete file in the slave. opSlaveFull : Operation is fail for the slave don't have enough space. opCopyToSlaveFailure : Operation is fail when copy file to the slave.

Hh3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.name: Hh3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode
Hh3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.description: Flash partition upgrade method, i.e., method by which new files can be downloaded into the partition. FLH stands for Flash Load Helper, a feature provided on run-from-Flash systems for upgrading Flash. This feature uses the bootstrap code in ROMs to help in automatic download. This object should be retrieved if the partition status is runFromFlash(2). If the partition status is readOnly(1), the upgrade method would depend on the reason for the readOnly status. For example, it may simply be a matter of installing the programming jumper, or it may require execution of a later version of software that supports the Flash chips. unknown - the current system image does not know how Flash can be programmed. A possible method would be to reload the ROM image and perform the upgrade manually. rxbootFLH - the Flash Load Helper is available to download files to Flash. A copy-to-flash command can be used and this system image will automatically reload the Rxboot image in ROM and direct it to carry out the download request. direct - will be done directly by this image.

Hh3cFlashPartitionStatus.name: Hh3cFlashPartitionStatus
Hh3cFlashPartitionStatus.description: If device is not programmable the value of it will be 'readOnly'; If the current image is running from this partition the value of it will be 'runFromFlash' If device is programmable the value of it will be 'readWrite'.

hh3cFlhSupportNum.name: hh3cFlhSupportNum
hh3cFlhSupportNum.description: Specifies the total number of flash which the system supported. The MIB should not be loaded if there is no flash in the system and so the value here will be a minimum of 1.

hh3cFlashTable.name: hh3cFlashTable
hh3cFlashTable.description: This table gives the properties of all the flashes on the system.

hh3cFlhIndex.name: hh3cFlhIndex
hh3cFlhIndex.description: The index of hh3cFlashTable. There are two parts for this index depicted as follows: 31 15 0 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ + entity index + random index + + ( bit 16..31 ) ( bit 0..15 ) + +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ From bit0 to bit15 (two bytes), it has a minimum value of 1, and maximum value of the same as the value of hh3cFlhSupportNum. From bit16 to bit31 (two bytes), it is the physical index the same as the entPhysicalIndex specified in ENTITY-MIB.

hh3cFlhSize.name: hh3cFlhSize
hh3cFlhSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash indexed by hh3cFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device. If the total size of the flash exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hh3cFlhHCSize specifies the actual size.

hh3cFlhPos.name: hh3cFlhPos
hh3cFlhPos.description: The position of the flash device in system. This object is an index of entPhysicalTable in ENTITY-MIB. If the value of this object is 0, the main processor is indicated.

hh3cFlhName.name: hh3cFlhName
hh3cFlhName.description: The flash name within the system.

hh3cFlhChipNum.name: hh3cFlhChipNum
hh3cFlhChipNum.description: The chip numbers in the flash.

hh3cFlhDescr.name: hh3cFlhDescr
hh3cFlhDescr.description: Description of the purpose of the flash in the system.

hh3cFlhInitTime.name: hh3cFlhInitTime
hh3cFlhInitTime.description: The initialization time for the flash component or partition, recorded using the system time. This will be the boot time for a fixed device. For a removable component or a partition, it will be the initialization time.

hh3cFlhRemovable.name: hh3cFlhRemovable
hh3cFlhRemovable.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be removed or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash device CAN be removed.

hh3cFlhPartitionBool.name: hh3cFlhPartitionBool
hh3cFlhPartitionBool.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be partitioned or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash CAN be partitioned.

hh3cFlhMinPartitionSize.name: hh3cFlhMinPartitionSize
hh3cFlhMinPartitionSize.description: Minimum partition size supported. If hh3cFlhDevicePartitionBool is false, the value of this object is the same as hh3cFlhSize.

hh3cFlhMaxPartitions.name: hh3cFlhMaxPartitions
hh3cFlhMaxPartitions.description: The maximum count of partitions which the system supports for this flash. If hh3cFlhPartitionBool is false, the object value is 1.

hh3cFlhPartitionNum.name: hh3cFlhPartitionNum
hh3cFlhPartitionNum.description: The actual number of partitions supported by the system for this flash. If hh3cFlhPartitionBool is false, this value is 1.

hh3cFlhKbyteSize.name: hh3cFlhKbyteSize
hh3cFlhKbyteSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash device indexed by hh3cFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device.

hh3cFlhHCSize.name: hh3cFlhHCSize
hh3cFlhHCSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash indexed by hh3cFlhIndex. This node is a 64-bit substitute for hh3cFlhSize.

hh3cFlhChipTable.name: hh3cFlhChipTable
hh3cFlhChipTable.description: Table of properties for all flash chips. Used mainly for diagnostics.

hh3cFlhChipID.name: hh3cFlhChipID
hh3cFlhChipID.description: The manufacturer code (the upper byte) and device code (the lower byte) for a chip. Unknown chip code is presented as 00:00.

hh3cFlhChipDescr.name: hh3cFlhChipDescr
hh3cFlhChipDescr.description: The description of the flash chip.

hh3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.name: hh3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit
hh3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of write times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

hh3cFlhChipWriteTimes.name: hh3cFlhChipWriteTimes
hh3cFlhChipWriteTimes.description: A count of write times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 25 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after a write operation, and report any errors accordingly.

hh3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.name: hh3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit
hh3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of erase times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

hh3cFlhChipEraseTimes.name: hh3cFlhChipEraseTimes
hh3cFlhChipEraseTimes.description: A count of erase times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 2000 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after an erase operation, and report any errors accordingly.

hh3cFlhPartitionTable.name: hh3cFlhPartitionTable
hh3cFlhPartitionTable.description: Properties for the flash partitions. Minimum of one entry in this table.

hh3cFlhPartitionEntry.name: hh3cFlhPartitionEntry
hh3cFlhPartitionEntry.description: An entry of the hh3cFlhPartitionTable.Indexed by flash number and partition number.

hh3cFlhPartIndex.name: hh3cFlhPartIndex
hh3cFlhPartIndex.description: An index which specifies a sequenced partition in the system.

hh3cFlhPartFirstChip.name: hh3cFlhPartFirstChip
hh3cFlhPartFirstChip.description: The first chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

hh3cFlhPartLastChip.name: hh3cFlhPartLastChip
hh3cFlhPartLastChip.description: The last chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

hh3cFlhPartSpace.name: hh3cFlhPartSpace
hh3cFlhPartSpace.description: The total space of the flash partition. The following should be satisfied: hh3cFlhPartSpace = n*hh3cFlhMinPartitionSize If the total size of the flash partition exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hh3cFlhPartHCSpace specifies the actual size.

hh3cFlhPartSpaceFree.name: hh3cFlhPartSpaceFree
hh3cFlhPartSpaceFree.description: The flash partition's free space. If the free space of the flash partition exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hh3cFlhPartHCSpaceFree specifies the actual free space.

hh3cFlhPartFileNum.name: hh3cFlhPartFileNum
hh3cFlhPartFileNum.description: The number of all the files in the flash partition.

hh3cFlhPartChecksumMethod.name: hh3cFlhPartChecksumMethod
hh3cFlhPartChecksumMethod.description: The Checksum method which the file system uses.

hh3cFlhPartUpgradeMode.name: hh3cFlhPartUpgradeMode
hh3cFlhPartUpgradeMode.description: The upgrade mode of the Flash partition

hh3cFlhPartName.name: hh3cFlhPartName
hh3cFlhPartName.description: The name of the flash partition given by the system.

hh3cFlhPartRequireErase.name: hh3cFlhPartRequireErase
hh3cFlhPartRequireErase.description: Shows whether a write operation is conditional on partition erase.

hh3cFlhPartFileNameLen.name: hh3cFlhPartFileNameLen
hh3cFlhPartFileNameLen.description: The maximum length of file name supported in the system.

hh3cFlhPartBootable.name: hh3cFlhPartBootable
hh3cFlhPartBootable.description: The value indicates whether the partition is a bootable partition. The true(1) value indicates a bootable partition.

hh3cFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt.name: hh3cFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt
hh3cFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt.description: The value indicates whether the partition is used in a global file operation. The true(1) value indicates that in one global file operation files will be copied to or deleted from this partition. When hh3cFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt in one entry is set to true(1), hh3cFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt in other entries with the same entity index will be set to false(0).

hh3cFlhPartHCSpace.name: hh3cFlhPartHCSpace
hh3cFlhPartHCSpace.description: The total space of the flash partition. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hh3cFlhPartSpace.

hh3cFlhPartHCSpaceFree.name: hh3cFlhPartHCSpaceFree
hh3cFlhPartHCSpaceFree.description: The flash partition's free space. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hh3cFlhPartSpace.

hh3cFlhFileEntry.name: hh3cFlhFileEntry
hh3cFlhFileEntry.description: An entry representing a file. Indexed using flash number, partition number, and file number.

hh3cFlhFileIndex.name: hh3cFlhFileIndex
hh3cFlhFileIndex.description: Index of the table, whose range is from 1 to 2147483647

hh3cFlhFileName.name: hh3cFlhFileName
hh3cFlhFileName.description: A valid file name supported by the file system.

hh3cFlhFileSize.name: hh3cFlhFileSize
hh3cFlhFileSize.description: The file size in bytes excluding the file header of file system. The value should be greater than zero. If the file size exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hh3cFlhFileHCSize specifies the actual size.

hh3cFlhFileStatus.name: hh3cFlhFileStatus
hh3cFlhFileStatus.description: The status should be as follows: deleted(1): The file is in recycle bin. invalidChecksum(2): The checksum of file is invalid; valid(3): A valid file.

hh3cFlhFileChecksum.name: hh3cFlhFileChecksum
hh3cFlhFileChecksum.description: The file checksum in the header of file.

hh3cFlhFileHCSize.name: hh3cFlhFileHCSize
hh3cFlhFileHCSize.description: The file size in bytes. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hh3cFlhFileSize.

hh3cFlhOpEntry.name: hh3cFlhOpEntry
hh3cFlhOpEntry.description: Note an operation can not be stopped until it is finished. If notification is configured, NMS will receive a notification at the end of the operation. Entries in the table will be removed automatically in 5 minutes. It can also be deleted by NMS directly.

hh3cFlhOperIndex.name: hh3cFlhOperIndex
hh3cFlhOperIndex.description: Specifies the index of an entry. It is a random value when creating an entry.

hh3cFlhOperType.name: hh3cFlhOperType
hh3cFlhOperType.description: Specifies the operation to be executed. net2FlashWithErase Copy a file to flash; erase flash beforehand. net2FlashWithoutErase Copy a file to flash; do not erase flash beforehand. flash2Net Copy a file from flash. delete Delete a file from flash, the file name is specified by hh3cFlhOperSourceFile; rename Change a file's name.

hh3cFlhOperProtocol.name: hh3cFlhOperProtocol
hh3cFlhOperProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol used to transfer file. The default protocol is ftp. when 'clusterftp' or 'clustertftp' is selected, the hh3cFlhOperServerAddress needn't be set, the server address can be acquired automatically, the value of hh3cFlhOperServerAddress is uncertain during operation. Both member switch and commander switch can use them if they support HGMP v2.

hh3cFlhOperServerAddress.name: hh3cFlhOperServerAddress
hh3cFlhOperServerAddress.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation. The default value is 255.255.255.255 This object is replaced by hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

hh3cFlhOperServerUser.name: hh3cFlhOperServerUser
hh3cFlhOperServerUser.description: When using ftp to transfer files, the user name must be specified through this node.

hh3cFlhOperPassword.name: hh3cFlhOperPassword
hh3cFlhOperPassword.description: Remote user password for copying via ftp protocol. Optionally, This object may be ignored for protocols other than ftp.

hh3cFlhOperSourceFile.name: hh3cFlhOperSourceFile
hh3cFlhOperSourceFile.description: Specifies the source file name to be transferred. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. It must be specified.

hh3cFlhOperDestinationFile.name: hh3cFlhOperDestinationFile
hh3cFlhOperDestinationFile.description: Specifies the destination file name. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. If it is not specified, the destination file name is the same as source file name for application.

hh3cFlhOperEndNotification.name: hh3cFlhOperEndNotification
hh3cFlhOperEndNotification.description: If the value of it is specified 'true', a notification will be generated at the end of the operation. Else no notification will be generated.

hh3cFlhOperProgress.name: hh3cFlhOperProgress
hh3cFlhOperProgress.description: The progress described as the time taken for the operation.

hh3cFlhOperRowStatus.name: hh3cFlhOperRowStatus
hh3cFlhOperRowStatus.description: The row status of this table entry.

hh3cFlhOperServerPort.name: hh3cFlhOperServerPort
hh3cFlhOperServerPort.description: The port of remote host acting as server for operation. If the value of this object is not specified, the server port is the known protocol port.

hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrType.name: hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrType
hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrType.description: The type of IP address for hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.

hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.name: hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev
hh3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation.

hh3cFlhOperSrvVPNName.name: hh3cFlhOperSrvVPNName
hh3cFlhOperSrvVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

hh3cFlhOperNotification.name: hh3cFlhOperNotification
hh3cFlhOperNotification.description: A hh3cFlhOperNotification is sent at the completion of a flash copy operation if hh3cFlhOperEndNotification is true.

hh3cFlhMIBCompliance.name: hh3cFlhMIBCompliance
hh3cFlhMIBCompliance.description: The statement of compliance for those implementing this MIB.

hh3cFlhGroup.name: hh3cFlhGroup
hh3cFlhGroup.description: A collection of objects on Flash level information.

hh3cFlhChipGroup.name: hh3cFlhChipGroup
hh3cFlhChipGroup.description: A collection of objects on chip level information.

hh3cFlhPartitionGroup.name: hh3cFlhPartitionGroup
hh3cFlhPartitionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing on partition level information.

hh3cFlhFileGroup.name: hh3cFlhFileGroup
hh3cFlhFileGroup.description: A collection of objects on file level information.

hh3cFlhOperationGroup.name: hh3cFlhOperationGroup
hh3cFlhOperationGroup.description: A collection of objects of flash operations.

hh3cFlhNotificationGroup.name: hh3cFlhNotificationGroup
hh3cFlhNotificationGroup.description: The collection of notifications in the module
